Mário Macilau: Circle of Memories
results.description:
In the framework of Africa2020 and Afriqu’à Nanterre, La Terrasse exhibits Mário Macilau's series "Circle of Memories", evoking the Portuguese colonial heritage of his country. 

The artist combines portraits with immediate surroundings and places in ruins, particularly buildings from the colonial period. Each photograph was carried out at the same break time, in a time of slow pause, which allows him to direct his lens first on people, and then on the scene, in reverse.

Photographs by Jamel Shabazz: 1980-1989
results.description: Jamel Shabazz was born and raised in Brooklyn, New York. At the young age of fifteen, he picked up his first camera and started his photographic journey. Since the early 1980s, Shabazz has captured the energy of street life in New York, making iconic images of community, joy, and style. The upcoming solo show Photographs by Jamel Shabazz: 1980–1989 brings together mostly unseen works from this era.

results.description: Marlborough New York is pleased to present Brassaï, an online exhibition of seminal photographs by the lauded Franco-Hungarian artist that redefined the collective perception of nocturnal Paris and its underground subcultures during the 1930s. Comprised of 39 photographs printed by the artist, the exhibition culls some of his most iconic images from the series Paris by Night, Secret Paris, Paris by Day, and The Artists of My Life.

results.title: Terry O'Neill | "A Tribute to Terry O'Neill"
Terry O'Neill Portraits
results.description: O’Neill began his career at the birth of the 1960s. While other photographers concentrated on earthquakes, wars, and politics, O’Neill realized that youth culture was a breaking news story on a global scale and began chronicling the emerging faces of film, fashion, and music who would go on to define the Swinging Sixties. By 1965 he was being commissioned by the biggest magazines and newspapers in the world.

results.title: A tribute to Terry O'Neill
